      "span_text": "The NMDA receptor is composed of an oligomer of neuromodulatory subunits including at least one NR1 entity necessary for channel function and several other sites termed NR2A-NR2D that associate to form the channel.  The regulatory subunits include a glycine-sensitive binding site, two voltage-sensitive magnesium and zinc sites (involved in blocking NMDA responses) and two polyamine sites (either stimulatory or inhibitory)."
